[We now understand why there has been a conspicuous absence of news on the
Nipah virus outbreak especially of human infections coming out from
Malaysia through the media although infection is still being detected among
pigs in pig farms in certain states. The answer lies in the last sentence:
"We contained the news because it is not necessary to alarm the public" in
the Penang Chief Minister's statement. I suppose this is the official stand
of the Malaysian government on the matter. - Mod.CYC
